The United States government established planning organizations to provide for the coordination of land use, transportation and infrastructure. These Metropolitan Planning Organizations (MPO) may exist as a separate, independent organization or they may be administered by a city, county, [[regional planning organization]], highway commission or other government organization.<ref>{{cite web|title=Regional Councils, COGs & MPOs|url=http://narc.org/about-narc/cogs-mpos/|website=National Association of Regional Councils|accessdate=17 November 2017}}</ref> Each MPO has its own structure and governance. The following is a list of the current federally designated MPOs.

