In [[telecommunication]], a '''stop signal''' is a [[Signalling (telecommunication)|signal]] that marks the end of part of a transmission, for example: #In [[asynchronous serial communication]], a signal at the end of a [[character (computing)|character]] that prepares the receiving device for the reception of a subsequent character. A stop signal is usually limited to one [[signal element]] having any duration equal to or greater than a specified minimum value. # A signal to a receiving mechanism to wait for the next signal.
